Descripción: A perfect integration of a Torque & Angle Digital Torque Wrench in Desoutter Ecosystem, securing 100% traceability of your manual tightening operations and Joint Checks.
Beneficios: - Secure your Safety and Quality Critical manual operations in difficult access conditions- Identification and enabling of the tool through Certificates- 100% traceability (Results & Curves)- Flexibility to fix NOK from previous stations in dynamic- Data usage for continous process improvements- Reduce your inventory of unaccurate mechanical wrenches and the calibration cost related- Flexibility in associating RFID TAG end -fittings to Psets to automatically ajust Torque and Angle related ratios- Activate features and strategies "A la carte" to fit your station requirements- Digital Twin : direct access to the full documention of the wrench for support and maintenance- Get alerts for calibrations and logs of your process modifications.
Caracteristicas: - Double transducer for category A tightenings and Joint checks).- Angular speed of the gyroscope up to 250°/second.- Execution of Assembly Processes with consecutive or parallel assembly actions.- Detection of NOK scenarios if there is a Rehit or an Overspeed during the tightening (reported to operator and in traceability)- Easy paring and rebalancing of the Digital Wrench Tightning Unit.- New WLAN Dual Band module with global certification- New Li-ion battery offering an autonomy of 8 hours in communication.- Visual (LEDs) feedback, doubled with a configurable vibration module to indicate the evolution of the torque applied.- Easy procedure for firmware upgrades in maintenance.
exactitud: +/-1% accuracy of the torque reading value from 10% to 100% of the max torque of the wrench.
name: Q SHIELD 30 C

Descripción: Torque & Angle Digital Torque Wrench for Quality Inpectors and Engineering. Ideal companion for Metrology : Joint Analysis / Joint Check
Beneficios: - Conduct Joint Analysis at Engineering stage to define tightening specifications for Production and build prototypes.- Conduct Process Capability Tests (PCT) with 6 Residual Torque Strategies (includes 5 methods from VDI-VDE 2645 - Part 3)- Perform drag torque test to measure the average / Min or Max torque over a specified angle.- 100% traceability of your tests (Results & Curves) by USB transfer into Delta QC Quality Software (Advanced version).- Flexibility in associating RFID TAG end -fittings to Tests Psets to automatically ajust Torque and Angle related ratios- Digital Twin : direct access to the full documention of the wrench for support and maintenance- Easy programing with pre-defined parameters for quick adjustments to your application.
Caracteristicas: - Double transducer for Tightening and Tests (Joint Analysis & Joint checks).- Angular speed of the gyroscope up to 250°/second.- Up to 250 Psets / 1000 results and 25 curves in wrench memory.- Compact versions up to 350 Nm (< 700 mm long) for 1 hand handling.- New Li-ion battery offering an autonomy of 8 hours in communication.- Visual (LEDs) feedback, doubled with a configurable vibration module to indicate the evolution of the torque applied.- Easy procedure for firmware upgrades in maintenance.
exactitud: +/-1% accuracy of the torque reading value from 10% to 100% of the max torque of the wrench.
name: Q SHIELD 30 S

Descripción: A perfect integration of a Torque & Angle Digital Torque Wrench in Desoutter Ecosystem, securing 100% traceability of your manual tightening operations and Joint Checks.
Beneficios: - Secure your Safety and Quality Critical manual operations in difficult access conditions- Identification and enabling of the tool through Certificates- 100% traceability (Results & Curves)- Flexibility to fix NOK from previous stations in dynamic- Data usage for continous process improvements- Reduce your inventory of unaccurate mechanical wrenches and the calibration cost related- Flexibility in associating RFID TAG end -fittings to Psets to automatically ajust Torque and Angle related ratios- Activate features and strategies "A la carte" to fit your station requirements- Digital Twin : direct access to the full documention of the wrench for support and maintenance- Get alerts for calibrations and logs of your process modifications.
Caracteristicas: - Double transducer for category A tightenings and Joint checks).- Angular speed of the gyroscope up to 250°/second.- Execution of Assembly Processes with consecutive or parallel assembly actions.- Detection of NOK scenarios if there is a Rehit or an Overspeed during the tightening (reported to operator and in traceability)- Easy paring and rebalancing of the Digital Wrench Tightning Unit.- New WLAN Dual Band module with global certification- New Li-ion battery offering an autonomy of 8 hours in communication.- Visual (LEDs) feedback, doubled with a configurable vibration module to indicate the evolution of the torque applied.- Easy procedure for firmware upgrades in maintenance.
exactitud: +/-1% accuracy of the torque reading value from 10% to 100% of the max torque of the wrench.
name: Q SHIELD 30 C

Descripción: The nature of the impulse tool itself is to deliver multiple torque pulses that accumulate clamp force in the joint. These pulses are difficult to measure. The FCT is a Transducer measuring the Clamping Force of a preset Pulse tool.
Beneficios: * Measures the repeatability of pulse tools to achieve a target clamping force.* By measuring the clamp force instead of the torque delivered, the adverse effects of adding an in-line torque transducer are eliminated.* As most design offices specify a clamping force, measuring the actual clamping force allows to eliminate the uncertitude linked to the translation in torque of a clamping value.
Caracteristicas: Accuracy +/-0,5% of Reading ValueBuilt-in Load CellUsed with Delta xD data collectors and cablesBattery powered with up to 12 hours autonomy Allows a display of both Clamping Force and Torque (K factor)Up to 2000 Hz filter selectionRS-232 interface to download readings in “real time”Large screen and easy to use menus (5 languages)Supplied with screw kit and 3/8” socket SW13
name: FCT30

Descripción: The nature of the impulse tool itself is to deliver multiple torque pulses that accumulate clamp force in the joint. These pulses are difficult to measure. The FCT is a Transducer measuring the Clamping Force of a preset Pulse tool.
Beneficios: * Measures the repeatability of pulse tools to achieve a target clamping force.* By measuring the clamp force instead of the torque delivered, the adverse effects of adding an in-line torque transducer are eliminated.* As most design offices specify a clamping force, measuring the actual clamping force allows to eliminate the uncertitude linked to the translation in torque of a clamping value.
Caracteristicas: Accuracy +/-0,5% of Reading ValueBuilt-in Load CellUsed with Delta xD data collectors and cablesBattery powered with up to 12 hours autonomy Allows a display of both Clamping Force and Torque (K factor)Up to 2000 Hz filter selectionRS-232 interface to download readings in “real time”Large screen and easy to use menus (5 languages)Supplied with screw kit and 3/8” socket SW18
name: FCT60
